                  </hi>. I am a licensed victualler, and live in Crutched Friars, On the 16th of May, about a quarter before eleven o'clock, I was passing London-bridge, felt something at my pocket, turned, and saw the prisoner and another boy—I said, "You have taken my handkerchief out of my pocket"—the prisoner ran off—the policeman took him by Fishmongers' Hall—this is my handkerchief.</p>
